{
  "stem": "22582.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they had cognac, most of the time-- all the good things, cognac, and cigarettes, and [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] chocolate.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when they, in our camp, they found out that they have all those things, we had to-- we had to sort it first, not that we had to-- they had to do too much forcing in this respect, because we were trying to help ourselves.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we took the cognac or cigarettes or whatever.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We brought it into the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And for this, we got soup, more soup, more bread.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And that's how we could survive pretty easily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now, don't forget that we had to-- to steal.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "We had two-- we had the SS guard for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We had to steal-- the guy from Organisation-- not the German, because he wouldn't think-- he thought that was the biggest crime.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But the Austrian, oh, he needed a lot of cigarettes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He was a chain smoker.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Then we had to bring to the camp for the German, for the real German, for the-- for the people who are running, the SS from the camp, and the people who are running the camp itself, which are not German.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So we had to sneak quite a bit in order to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And they knew exactly when the came, what every train had.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And that's how we-- and so the-- my-- our SS man, our guard, had to watch us from the SS man who was coming with a friend, with the train, because when he would find us stealing, that would be the end of whoever stole.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So everybody was watching somebody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And that's-- we where there for nine months.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
